          protected final java.lang.Object readResolve()

        • writeObject

          private void writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream rOut)
                  throws java.io.IOException
          Serializes this instance into the given stream.
          Serial Data:
          First writes out the default form of the non-transient fields, followed by the count of all steps in this process and the steps themselves. After this the size of the execution stack, the names of the steps on it (from bottom to top) and finally the name of the current step is written.
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException - In case of I/O errors
